# 10 — Safety Standard

## Layer safety ownership

| Layer | Safety role |
|-------|-------------|
| STM32 | Safety-relevant real-time, VCM, power enable chain, kill interaction |
| ESP32 | **Never safety-critical** |
| Tablet / Web UI | **Never required** for vehicle operation |
| ECU | Engine protection algorithms only; not body loads |

## Fail operational

ESP32, tablet, or Wi-Fi loss shall not stop engine, pumps, cooling execution per VCM/rules.

## Per-function safe state

Do **not** assume “all outputs OFF” is universally safe. Each function needs defined reaction for:

ECU power · fuel pump · coolant pump · fans · lighting · EHPS · wipers · isolation circuits

Missing reaction → report as **OPEN ISSUE**.

## Kill / isolation

Competition battery-isolation and engine-stop shall not depend solely on STM32, ESP32, CAN, or Web UI. Regulations and alternator isolation — TBD in SRS.

## Configuration safety

Config shall not override hardware channel capability, current ceilings, PWM limits, retry limits, or revision compatibility.

## Testing

DevKit gate before vehicle (EDL-014). Fail-operational tests in `docs/008` Phase D.

Refs: `docs/001` § safety, `docs/002` §9, `docs/008` §11.
